        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 5 at 5:58PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 558 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Organ Cave, or over Ronceverte, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Alleghany...
Lewisburg...
White Sulphur Springs...
Ronceverte...
Greenbrier River Trail...
Lewisburg Airport...
and Alvon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
